The Kentucky Proud™ Advisory Council is hereby created for the purpose of advising the department concerning the implementation and administration of the Kentucky Proud™ Program authorized by KRS 260.017. The council shall consist of the following twelve (12) members:
Commissioner, or the Commissioner's designee, who shall serve as chair and who shall appoint the members in subparagraphs 3. to 11. of this paragraph;
Dean, University of Kentucky College of Agriculture, or the dean's representative;
One (1) farmer member of the Kentucky Proud™ Program;
One (1) Kentucky food retailer;
One (1) Kentucky food distributor;
One (1) Kentucky food processor;
One (1) Kentucky agritourism venue operator;
One (1) representative of a Kentucky agriculture commodity organization;
One (1) Kentucky restaurateur;
One (1) producer of a Kentucky Proud™ product; and
Two (2) at-large members.
